# Launch Folder

This folder contains the launch files used for the Robotics AI project.

In ROS 2, launch files are used to start multiple nodes or system components together. Instead of running every node manually in separate terminals, a launch file helps start the required parts of the project in a more organized way.

## Purpose of This Folder

The main purpose of this folder is to support the execution of the robotics AI pipeline.

The launch files help bring up important components such as ROS 2 nodes, simulation-related nodes, localization support, and control-related modules. This makes it easier to test the system as one connected workflow.

## Why Launch Files Are Important

Launch files are useful because robotics systems usually depend on many nodes running at the same time.

For example, this project includes different parts such as:

- ROS 2 communication nodes,
- localization and TF nodes,
- AI decision-making nodes,
- PX4 control nodes,
- and simulation bridge-related components.

Running these separately can become difficult and confusing. Launch files help manage this process by starting the required nodes together.

## Role in the Project

This folder supports the project by making the system easier to run, test, and demonstrate.

The launch files help connect the different parts of the pipeline, including simulation, ROS 2 communication, AI decision logic, and PX4 control.

